
[1]akin

   AKIN', a. [a or of and kin. See Kin.]

   1. Related by blood, used of persons; as, the two families are near
   akin.

   2. Allied by nature; partaking of the same properties; as, envy and
   jealousy are near akin. [This adjective is used only after the noun.]
